LM example - The Vocab Dataset

Set-up

Ensure you have the ggplot2, dplyr and car packages installed before trying to render this document in HTML.

The Data

glimpse(Vocab)
## Rows: 30,351
## Columns: 4
## $ year       <dbl> 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974, 1974,
## $ sex        <fct> Male, Male, Female, Female, Female, Male, Male, Male, Femal
## $ education  <dbl> 14, 16, 10, 10, 12, 16, 17, 10, 12, 11, 6, 5, 11, 12, 14, 1
## $ vocabulary <dbl> 9, 9, 9, 5, 8, 8, 9, 5, 3, 5, 5, 5, 6, 5, 5, 1, 4, 1, 1, 3,

The model

# y ~ x
my_model <- lm(vocabulary ~ education, data = Vocab)
summary(my_model)
##

Coefficients:

1.6779 0.3319

ggplot(Vocab, aes(x = education, y = vocabulary)) +
  geom_jitter(shape = 16, alpha = 0.4) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Predict

Manually:

# score: 6 years of edu
1.6779 + 0.3319 * 6
## [1] 3.6693

Using the extracted coefficients

edu <- 6
b_0 <- coefficients(my_model)[1]
b_1 <- coefficients(my_model)[2]

b_0 + b_1 * edu
## (Intercept) 
##    3.669181

Using the predict() function:

predict(my_model, data.frame(education = 6))
##        1 
## 3.669181
